main event: A witness observed a flying object described as a 'flying saucer' near Three Lakes, Wisconsin on July 17, 1963.
interesting points: The object was seen at approximately 1 o'clock in the morning,It was described as globular in shape and glittering,The object was estimated to be one mile away and moved faster than a plane,The witness mentioned that it did not resemble any known aircraft or helicopter,The sighting was documented in a report sent to the Air Force for investigation.
witness description: The witness was staying at an aunt's near Bridgeport Cottage and described the area as mostly wooded.
